  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Users can save Quick Sale, Repair, and Trade-in tickets as quotes, which enables tickets to be saved and re-opened later without affecting inventory levels. Quotes also use the same status system that you use for tickets and repairs. Converting a quote into an active ticket is a one-click process, and once converted, the related inventory is immediately pulled to the ticket.</p><ul><li><p>When negotiating a repair, sale, or trade-in with a customer, a staff member can save a quote and leave the ticket while the customer shops or considers a deal. Previously, a trade-in ticket had to be closed with a transaction before the user could leave the ticket.</p><ul><li><p>Inventory items added to the ticket are not pulled from inventory, and trade-in items added to the ticket will not be added to inventory.</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Quotes are not included in revenue reports, since the transaction has not been completed. Revenue reporting only looks at <strong>Tickets in Closed status</strong>.</p></li><li><p>The ability to save a ticket as a quote can be toggled on/off.</p><ul><li><p>Admins can toggle this selection at the Company level, affecting all locations, or override this decision at the Location level.</p></li><li><p>By default, RepairQ has this feature disabled. This article includes instructions on how to allow this feature.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3 id=\"Quotes:SaveaTicketasaQuote-Tipsforsavingaticketasaquote\">Tips for saving a ticket as a quote</h3><ul><li><p>You can only save a ticket as a quote <strong>before</strong> saving it as another status. If a ticket has already been progressed to a status, it cannot be reverted to a quote.</p></li><li><p>Save as Quote is available in the ticket workflow as long as a customer and item have been added.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"Quotes:SaveaTicketasaQuote-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933246809\" rel=\"nofollow\">RepairQ Opportunities (Quotes)</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1934458927\" rel=\"nofollow\">Contacts Overview</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1934917634\" rel=\"nofollow\">Quotes: Convert a Quote to a Ticket</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934491696/Appointments\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934491696\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Appointment Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933246465\" rel=\"nofollow\">Automated Notification Resources</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2022080562/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Quotes:SaveaTicketasaQuote-Allow\u201cSaveasQuote\u201dforTickets\">Allow \u201cSave as Quote\u201d for Tickets</h2><p /><p>Log into RepairQ as a user with Admin access. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings </strong>\u2192 <strong>Location Settings</strong>. On the Settings Overview screen, scroll until you find the <strong>Tickets </strong>section. Under this category, click <strong>General Settings</strong>.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: An admin can enable this feature for all locations by navigating to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Company Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2022080562/Quote%2011.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"544\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2022080562/Quote%2012.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>When viewing the Ticket General Settings page, turn off the toggle for <strong>\u2018Disable \u201cSave as quote\u201d button on new tickets.\u2019</strong> Once you have made your selection, click <strong>Save </strong>to submit your changes.</p><ul><li><p>Toggle this setting <strong>ON </strong>(default)<strong> </strong>to <strong>disable </strong>the ability to save tickets as quotes.</p></li><li><p>Toggle this setting <strong>OFF </strong>to <strong>enable </strong>saving tickets as quotes.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Ticket Settings.png\" width=\"579\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2022080562/Ticket%20Settings.png?api=v2\"></span><hr/><h2 id=\"Quotes:SaveaTicketasaQuote-ConvertaTickettoaQuote\">Convert a Ticket to a Quote</h2><p>When creating a new ticket, and you link a customer and add a Repair Device or Ticket Item, the option to save the ticket as a quote will be available along the bottom row of ticket statuses.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2022080562/Quote%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>The quote will be saved in New status and you can find the ticket in Quote List or by filtering the Ticket List for quotes.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2022080562/Quote%2014.png?api=v2\"></span><p> </p><p /><p>START 1.20.X</p>",
